  <li id="comment-10391" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Susan Parran</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/07/a-bold-statement/#comment-10391"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-07-16T17:53:00-04:00">Wednesday, July 16, 2008 at 5:53 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>The flours: It&#8217;s all got to do with those long-chain proteins! Low-protein flours create that alternate cookie universe, and that &#8220;crumb&#8221; texture that bakers so often talk about (versus the chewy feel of cookies baked using more gluten-rich flours). You can do the same thing for shortbread- just substitute a little rice flour for a portion of the all-purpose flour. You won&#8217;t believe the difference &#8211; almost a melting sensation on the tongue.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
