    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/06972626132073744817" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">kayenne</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/07/a-bold-statement/#comment-10416"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-07-19T01:22:00-04:00">Saturday, July 19, 2008 at 1:22 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>dunno if anyone mentioned this yet, but just a thought… why not scoop out and ball the dough first before refrigerating? that way, you’ll just have to plunk it down onto the baking sheet. the dough should be stiff enough to hold its form even if you stack them all in a bowl.</></>while you’re at it, make double or triple batch… after the required refrigeration, stick the rest in a freezer bag and freeze. instant cookies next time you crave some. and having it pre-scooped means you can take out only the number of cookies that you want.</p>
    </div>

