      <p>You can definitely use all-purpose flour for this recipe. I made this over the weekend and 3 3/4 cups ap flour is the amount you need for this recipe. I would not use the full amount of choc chips this recipe calls for again, way too much for my taste, may be a llittle over a pound. Also, if you are looking for choc chip cookie recipe you don&#8217;t need the dough for try Dorie Greenspan&#8217;s My Best Choc Chip Cookies from her Baking cookbook, that is my go to recipe for choc chip cookies.</></>Jen B</p>
