    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Rachel, I&#8217;m so glad you liked the oatmeal cookies!  As for the salt here, yes, if you don&#8217;t have a coarse type, you should probably reduce it a bit.  I&#8217;m not sure how much, but you could try doing a Google search for how to replace kosher salt with table salt.  Or you could just wing it!  </></>E, many recipes call for unsalted butter and then add salt because it&#8217;s more precise.  It&#8217;s hard to quantify the amount of salt in salted butter.</></>JT, we live in Ballard, and we generally buy it at the Safeway at Market and 15th Avenue.</p>
    </div>

