  <li id="comment-10461" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/07/a-bold-statement/#comment-10461"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-08-17T16:45:00-04:00">Sunday, August 17, 2008 at 4:45 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>K., I&#8217;m not sure what happened with yours!  They should not be flat, no &#8211; they should be a little on the thick side, actually, with nice crinkles on top.  Hmm.  Could your baking soda or baking powder be old?  That might be the culprit.  Also, how cold was the dough when you baked it?  If the dough isn&#8217;t cool or cold, it could tend to spread more and seem flatter. Just a couple of guesses&#8230;</p>
